{"word":"νέκυς","slug":"νέκυς","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>νέκυς</b></el> <el>(νέκυς, υος, ὁ,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>like <a href='S:νεκρός'><el>νεκρός</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>a dead body, a corpse, corse</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:— in <a href='S:plural'>pl.</a> <i>the spirits of the dead</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>Manes, inferi</el>, in <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>as <a href='S:Adjective'>adj.</a> <i>dead</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}